.competency_report_guideline
  %h1.blue_heading.large-text.font-normal
    Guidelines to Interpret the Report
  .divider2
  
  .suitability-competency-report-guideline
    .section_01
      .title
        .index-holder.pull-left
          .rounded
            1
        .title-text.pull-left Scale and Scores Overview
        .clr
      .divider1
      .box-bordered.span10{:style=>"margin:0 0 0 25px;padding: 14px 10px"}
        Jombay's assessments are built around 6-point scales ranging from Low to High.
      .dot-nav.span1.first{:style=>"margin-top: 19px;"}
        .rounded
      .scale.pull-right
        .line
        .marker-container
          - @norm_buckets.each do |norm_bucket|
            .marker
              - if norm_bucket.name.split(" ").size == 1
                %br/
              = norm_bucket.name
          .clr
      .clr
    .divider2
    .section_02
      .black.line-height2.pull-left 
        Interpersonal Relations and Emotional Control
      .scale.pull-right
        .line
        .marker-container
          .marker
          .marker
          .marker.active
            .inn Average (Low)
          .marker
          .marker
          .marker
          .clr
      .clr
    .divider1
    .box-bordered.span{:style=>"margin:0 0 0 25px;"}
      Competency Overview section gives you your scores in each of the competencies
    .dot-nav.divider1.pull-left{:style=>"width: 165px; margin-top: -4px;"}
      .rounded
    .clr

    .divider2

    .section_03
      .title
        .index-holder.pull-left
          .rounded
            2
        .title-text.pull-left Competencies Overview
        .clr
      .divider1

      .frame.text-center
        .heading.pull-left
          Task Management
        .heading.pull-right
          Average (Low)
        .clr

        .pull-left.left-offset1
          .dot-nav.left.divider1.span1{:style=>"margin-top: 7px;"}
            .rounded
          .box-bordered.span{:style=>"margin:10px 0 0 0;"}
            Name of the Competency measured
          .clr
        .pull-right.right-offset1
          .box-bordered.span{:style=>"margin:10px 0 0 0;"}
            Your score on this Competency 
          .dot-nav.divider1.first.span1{:style=>"margin-top: 7px;"}
            .rounded
          .clr
        .clr
        .divider1
        .span13.margin-auto
          = wicked_pdf_image_tag ("report/pdf/interpretation_guideline_hexagon.png")
        .bottom-tag.margin-auto.divider1.span14
          .divider1
          .text.span5.margin-auto
            Traits Under the Competency
        .divider2
    .divider3
    .section_04
      .title
        .index-holder.pull-left
          .rounded
            3
        .title-text.pull-left Scores on Traits
        .clr
      .divider2
      .interpretation_guideline_trait
        .box-bordered.black.span
          Traits are behavioral characteristics evaluated in the assessment. To know the 
          %br/
          meaning of a Trait, simply place your cursor over it to see a text-box with its definition
        .box-bordered.span5.pull-right{:style=>"margin-top: -14px"}
          Displayed here is what you scored on this Trait in the assessment. 
        .clr
      .box-bordered.span.text-center{:style=>"margin-top: -30px"}
        This text helps you understand the significance of your score on this trait.
      .box-bordered.span7.pull-right{:style=>"margin-top: -30px; border-color: #1d78be"}
        Expected Score: This is the expected score range for 
        a trait in a particular profile. This determines whether a trait has a Favourable score or a Less Favourable  score.
      .clr
      .divider2